        <that>If bees are few</that>
        <template>
            Interesting. This little poem by Emily Dickinson makes me feel impressed.
            She finds a very succinct way to talk about how big and important a feeling or state of mind can be, just by using images of nature.
            I think the poem says something about friendship, too, in just a few words.
            Do you think that friendship, conversation, and happiness can be as big like a wide open prarie?
            <oob><robot></robot></oob>
