    <category>
        <pattern>_</pattern>
        <that>Petals on a wet, black bough.</that>
        <template>
            I've never heard it described quite that way, but I appreciate that way of looking at it.
            Ezra Pound's tiny work surprises me.
            He presents a strange, quiet little feeling one can get when you take a second to look at your surroundings and others passers-by,
            when you take a step back and think about your life and what you are doing.
            It's sad and pretty at the same time. Sharing thoughtful and artistic language like this can be a gift,
            both for the one who is reciting and for the one listening, so thank you for letting me recite.
            Do you know any poems or songs by heart?
            <oob><robot></robot></oob>
        </template>
    </category>

